05:28.020 --> 05:29.590
so how does this work?

05:29.590 --> 05:32.470
It's pretty cut and dried.
The prisoner is announced by the parole board.

05:32.470 --> 05:36.360
He's given an opportunity to make his statement--
express remorse for his crimes.

05:36.360 --> 05:39.830
Once the board has her his request,
they'll ask if we have any objections.

05:42.620 --> 05:45.550
Tell us about the crime
you committed,mr. Cosgrove.

05:46.540 --> 05:48.300
I shot my wife.

05:50.160 --> 05:53.990
You shot her 16 times,mr. Cosgrove,
in the back.

05:54.380 --> 05:56.240
You killed her.

05:57.330 --> 05:59.960
What the board needs to
determine at this time

05:59.960 --> 06:03.590
is do you regret that you
committed this crime?

06:03.800 --> 06:06.920
I do,sir.I regret it every day
of my life.

06:06.920 --> 06:10.350
I'm a very different man
from the one who arrived here ten years ago.

06:10.350 --> 06:14.320
I work hard to be a better person.
I gave my life over to the lord.

06:15.980 --> 06:18.120
Would the state
care to comment?

06:19.400 --> 06:21.060
Due to the heinous nature
of this crime,

06:21.060 --> 06:23.810
as well as to the fact
that,to my recollection,

06:23.810 --> 06:27.050
this prisoner has never
shown any remorse before this hearing,

06:27.050 --> 06:30.510
the state would ask that parole
be denied at this time.

06:31.590 --> 06:34.960
The board is inclined to agree.
Parole is denied.

06:34.960 --> 06:36.930
Don't worry,just
onmore to go.

06:36.930 --> 06:40.600
The board will now
consider the petition of mr. Sam elkin.

06:41.070 --> 06:42.980
You've served five years
of a life sentence,

06:42.980 --> 06:47.180
and this is the first time you've been eligible
to appear before the parole board,correct?

06:47.180 --> 06:50.190
Yes,sir.
That's correct,sir.

06:50.190 --> 06:52.850
Tell us about
your crime,mr. Elkin.

06:54.840 --> 06:56.630
Mr. Elkin?

06:57.960 --> 07:00.080
You know what I did.

07:00.080 --> 07:03.230
It's important that
we hear it from you.

07:05.840 --> 07:08.790
I guess I kidnapped
my girlfriend...

07:08.790 --> 07:11.350
my ex-girlfriend.

07:12.610 --> 07:14.720
We broke up
about a month before...

07:14.720 --> 07:18.150
she broke up-- it was her idea.

07:19.400 --> 07:22.230
I wait for her in her car.
I had a key.

07:22.230 --> 07:25.960
She used to let me use it.
Anyway,I waited for her.

07:27.020 --> 07:30.300
I knew she'd be going out.
It was tuesday.

07:30.670 --> 07:33.520
She always went out on tuesdays.

07:35.320 --> 07:37.980
I forced her to drive
out into the desert.

07:37.980 --> 07:40.360
And once
we were there,

07:40.360 --> 07:43.380
we... we did it.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.450
I... I made her do it.

07:47.980 --> 07:50.370
When we were done,I just,

07:50.680 --> 07:53.560
uh,started choking her.

07:53.820 --> 07:57.280
She was tiny.
It didn't take long.

07:58.730 --> 08:00.690
It was almost
morning by then,

08:00.690 --> 08:05.790
so I drove her car back into the city
with her dead body in the passenger seat.

08:06.920 --> 08:10.770
Pulled into a busy car wash
on bell road.

08:11.400 --> 08:15.330
The kind with two lanes--
one where they clean the inside,

08:15.330 --> 08:19.860
and an express where the car just goes
through unattended and they clean the outside.

08:21.000 --> 08:23.970
Once the car
was inside the wash,

08:23.970 --> 08:27.280
I,uh,just turned
and walked away.

08:38.929 --> 08:41.659
that's what you needed
to hear,right?

08:43.100 --> 08:46.860
It's my understanding that until you became
eligible for parole this month,

08:46.860 --> 08:50.940
you repeatedly denied
committing any of these crimes.

08:50.940 --> 08:52.810
Uh,yes,sir.

08:52.810 --> 08:55.440
And I regret that,sir.

08:55.440 --> 08:58.000
Mr. District attorney?

09:00.230 --> 09:03.850
While I am moved to finally hear mr. Elkin
admit to these heinous acts,

09:03.850 --> 09:06.740
I can't help but be suspicious
of his motives.

09:06.740 --> 09:10.550
Mr. Elkin is,after all,well aware that
taking responsibility for his crimes

09:10.550 --> 09:13.610
is a condition
of his parole eligibility.

09:13.790 --> 09:16.710
Perhaps his apology
and remorse will carry more weight

09:16.710 --> 09:19.540
when he has another five
years to sleep on them.

09:29.330 --> 09:30.770
hello?

10:09.920 --> 10:11.500
I'm lonely.

10:11.500 --> 10:14.160
Hi,lonely.
My name's joe.

10:14.160 --> 10:18.460
So what do you think? What are the chances
i'll see you before today becomes tomorrow?

10:19.540 --> 10:22.680
Uh,you wouldn't happen to know
what the temperature in hell is,would you?

10:22.680 --> 10:25.780
You haven't heard anything about
a big freeze,maybe?

10:25.780 --> 10:28.660
